## Testing the PKCE flow

The **Authorize** button above already performs the PKCE handshake automatically for the interactive flow. The recipe below is only needed to exercise the raw **POST /oauth/token** form by hand.

**1. Generate a code_verifier and code_challenge.** Paste this into your browser dev-tools console:

    (async()=>{const u=b=>btoa(String.fromCharCode(...new Uint8Array(b))).replaceAll('+','-').replaceAll('/','_').replaceAll('=','');const v=u(crypto.getRandomValues(new Uint8Array(32)));const c=u(await crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256',new TextEncoder().encode(v)));console.log('code_verifier :',v);console.log('code_challenge:',c);})();

**2. Authorize.** Open this URL in a new browser tab, substituting the code_challenge printed in step 1:

    /oauth/authorize?response_type=code&client_id={{kebabCase serviceName}}-client&redirect_uri=http://localhost:3000/docs/oauth2-redirect.html&code_challenge=CODE_CHALLENGE&code_challenge_method=S256&state=xyz

You are redirected to the seeded redirect URI with a **code** query parameter.

**3. Exchange the code for tokens.** Copy that **code**, then call **POST /oauth/token** (the endpoint below, or via curl) with: grant_type=authorization_code, code=COPIED_CODE, code_verifier=THE_VERIFIER_FROM_STEP_1, and redirect_uri=http://localhost:3000/docs/oauth2-redirect.html (the same value used in step 2).
`{{/ifEquals}},
